    "body": "**Description of the problem**\r\nAccording to the documentation for Figure.Legend:\r\n\r\n> spec (None or [str](https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#str)) \u2013 Either None [default] for using the automatically generated legend specification file, or a filename pointing to the legend specification file.\r\n\r\nWhich would imply to me that if I give a filename, it should use that file _instead of_ the auto-generated legend. However, this does not appear to happen - the auto-generated legend is used instead.\r\n\r\n**Full code that generated the error**\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport pygmt\r\n\r\nbounds = [-180.7568317475191,\r\n          -178.59975221352386,\r\n          51.37616035103776,\r\n          52.375229777638786]\r\n\r\nfig = pygmt.Figure()\r\nfig.basemap(projection=\"M10i\", region=bounds, frame=('WeSn', 'afg'))\r\n\r\nsta_x = -179\r\nfig.plot(x = [sta_x, ], y = [52, ], style = 'a16p', color = 'red', label = \"Wrong_1\")\r\nsta_x = 179.75\r\nfig.plot(x = [sta_x, ], y = [52, ], style = 't16p', color = 'green', label = \"Wrong_2\")\r\n\r\npos = 'JTR+jTR+o0.2c+l1.5'\r\n\r\ntest_file = \"/Users/israel/Desktop/legend.txt\"\r\n\r\n# Specifying a file as the first argument should over-ride the auto legend.\r\nfig.legend(test_file, position = pos, box = \"+gwhite+p1p\", verbose = True)\r\n\r\nfig.show(method = \"external\")\r\n```\r\nWhere the contents of `/Users/israel/Desktop/legend.txt` are:\r\n```\r\nS - kvolcano 0.222222i red - - Plot1\r\nS - kvolcano 0.222222i green - - Plot2\r\n```\r\nThis produces the following image:\r\n[7c3501330b2748ab827da002c428cde0.pdf](https://github.com/GenericMappingTools/pygmt/files/8393254/7c3501330b2748ab827da002c428cde0.pdf)\r\n\r\nRemoving the `label` argument from both plot commands allows the legend to properly use the file as expected.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Full error message**\r\n\r\nNo error message is generated, however the verbose output of `legend` indicates it is using the auto-generated file rather than the user-specified one:\r\n\r\n```\r\nlegend [INFORMATION]: Processing input text table data\r\nlegend [INFORMATION]: Processing hidden legend specification file /Users/israel/.gmt/sessions/gmt_session.22260/gmt.1.legend\r\nlegend [INFORMATION]: Reading Data Table from File /Users/israel/.gmt/sessions/gmt_session.22260/gmt.1.legend\r\nlegend [INFORMATION]: Central meridian not given, default to -179.678\r\nlegend [INFORMATION]: Map scale is 9.45374 km per cm or 1:945374.\r\nlegend [INFORMATION]: Legend height not given, using estimated height of 1.40367 cm.\r\nplot [INFORMATION]: Processing input table data\r\nplot [INFORMATION]: Map scale is 0.001 km per inch or 1:39.3701.\r\nplot [INFORMATION]: Reading Data Table from memory reference supplied by pointer\r\ntext [INFORMATION]: Processing input text table data\r\ntext [INFORMATION]: Map scale is 0.000393701 km per cm or 1:39.3701.\r\ntext [INFORMATION]: Reading Data Table from memory reference supplied by pointer\r\ntext [INFORMATION]: pstext: Plotted 2 text strings\r\n```\r\n\r\n**System information**\r\n\r\nPlease paste the output of `python -c \"import pygmt; pygmt.show_versions()\"`:\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport pygmt\r\n\r\nbounds = [-180.7568317475191,\r\n          -178.59975221352386,\r\n          51.37616035103776,\r\n          52.375229777638786]\r\n\r\nfig = pygmt.Figure()\r\nfig.basemap(projection=\"M10i\", region=bounds, frame=('WeSn', 'afg'))\r\n\r\nsta_x = -179\r\nfig.plot(x = [sta_x, ], y = [52, ], style = 'a16p', color = 'red', label = \"Wrong_1\")\r\nsta_x = 179.75\r\nfig.plot(x = [sta_x, ], y = [52, ], style = 't16p', color = 'green', label = \"Wrong_2\")\r\n\r\npos = 'JTR+jTR+o0.2c+l1.5'\r\n\r\ntest_file = \"/Users/israel/Desktop/legend.txt\"\r\n\r\n# Specifying a file as the first argument should over-ride the auto legend.\r\nfig.legend(test_file, position = pos, box = \"+gwhite+p1p\", verbose = True)\r\n\r\nfig.show(method = \"external\")\r\n```\r\n",
