            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Sorry, took me a while to look at this.  I looked at the legend documentation and I cannot find anywhere that says the spec file replaces entries created via -l.  The documentation says -M controls if both file and hidden info is used or just hidden [default].  Nothing about ignoring hidden info.  Why use -l if you are not going to use it?  We could certainly add a flag to -M to mean that, but is that really a good system?\r\n",
